The Express handler below lets a logged-in user search their own documents and open one by ID. It contains at least four distinct security vulnerabilities spanning multiple OWASP categories. Identify each vulnerability, name the OWASP category, and rewrite the handler to fix all of them.

```typescript
app.get('/docs/search', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const { q, sort, id } = req.query;
  if (id) {
    const doc = await db.query(
      `SELECT * FROM docs WHERE id = ${id}`
    );
    res.send(`<h1>${doc[0].title}</h1><div>${doc[0].body}</div>`);
    return;
  }
  const rows = await db.query(
    `SELECT id, title FROM docs WHERE title LIKE '%${q}%' ORDER BY ${sort}`
  );
  res.json(rows);
});
```

